<F P=101> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rossiya Bloc Victor in Crimea Poll </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2903093594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 29 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2903093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Nikolay Semena: "Crimea: `Rossiya' Party Bloc </F>
Wins Elections"] 
  [Text] Simferopol -- According to preliminary information, 
the greatest number of deputies' seats at the elections to the 
Crimean Supreme Council held 27 March were won by the "Rossiya" 
bloc of parties. The Communist Party of Crimea was in second 
place, and the Party for the Economic Revival of Crimea came 
third. Around 59 percent of the 1.8 million voters took part in 
the elections. 

</TEXT>

