<F P=101> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meshkov's Edict on Military `Unlawful' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2803171594 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 25 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2803171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Yet Another Unlawful Edict Issued by </F>
Yu. Meshkov"] 
  [Text] President of the Crimean Republic Yuriy Meshkov has 
issued an edict to have all the conscripts of the spring call-up 
do their military service in the Crimea only. The acting prime 
minister of the Crimea, Anatoliy Franchuk, and Military 
Commissioner Oleksandr Volkov were authorized to implement the 
edict. In this connection, Volkov told our correspondent that 
he had received the edict in the evening of 23 March. Just like 
Ukraine's Defense Minister Radetskyy, with whom O. Volkov 
discussed the subject, he considers the edict absolutely 
unlawful. "We will act in conformity with Ukraine's 
legislation," stressed Volkov. "As before, 80 percent of the 
conscripts will serve outside the Crimea and 20 percent (those 
found unfit for health reasons and the Crimean Tatars) will 
serve in the Crimea." 

</TEXT>

