<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Meets With Rybkin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803201494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1755 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2803201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Speaker of the State Duma Ivan Rybkin said that 
cooperation between the Russian and Kazakh parliaments should 
contribute to preservation of a single economic space. "We can 
encourage this process by lessening legislative differences," he 
told journalists on Monday after a meeting with Kazakh President 
Nursultan Nazarbayev in the Kremlin residence. 
  "We parliamentarians should prevent the legislations of our 
two countries, Russia and Kazakhstan, from getting too different 
from each other, so that it would be difficult to unify them 
later," Rybkin pointed out. He expressed the opinion that 
"political approaches to closer cooperation, to cooperation on 
the basis of equal rights and mutual respect for the sovereignty 
of the two countries are not far away. But, let me repeat, the 
path to that lies through cooperation in the sphere of economy." 
This was the main issue of the conversation with Nursultan 
Nazarbayev, Rybkin said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

