<H3> <TI>   Ministries Respond to U.S. Budget Amendment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903100194 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1000 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The American Congress has adopted an amendment to 
the draft budget for next year. It states that the USA will 
resist attempts by the Russian Federation to intimidate, to use 
military force, or economic pressure to create a sphere of 
influence in the former republics of the USSR and also in the 
countries of central and Eastern Europe. The Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs and the Ministry of Defense of Russia responded urgently 
to this decision today, by issuing a joint statement. It says 
that Russia is not setting its efforts against anyone at all and 
is not demanding special status or an exclusive role for itself. 

</TEXT>

