<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev: Joining NATO `in Future' Not Ruled Out </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2603160094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1358 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2603160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by special ITAR-TASS correspondents Vasiliy Belousov </F>
and Dmitriy Gorokhov] 
  [Text] Murmansk, 26 Mar -- We do not rule out Russia 
joining NATO in future, nor that this organization could undergo 
some transformation. But at the present time it is not a matter 
of bloc membership, but of cooperation. Herein lies the meaning 
of us joining the Partnership for Peace program, which will take 
place in the near future. This was stated by Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev when explaining Russia's approach to 
interrelations with the North Atlantic Union during a brief 
conversation with Russian and Norwegian journalists. 
  The minister also noted the contacts and ties between Russia 
and NATO, which are already developing ; the joint Pomor-94 
naval exercises that ended recently were an example of this. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

