<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Aide, CSCE Official Discuss Ethnic Russians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803193394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1755 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2803193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Max van der Stoel, high commissioner for national 
minorities of the Conference on Security and Cooperation in 
Europe (CSCE), on Monday had a meeting in Moscow with Georgiy 
Satarov, aide to the Russian president. 
  A source in Satarov's office told Interfax the meeting had 
focused on the position of ethnic Russians in various former 
Soviet republics, such as the Baltic states, Ukraine and 
Kazakhstan. 
  Satarov said that, despite some obstacles, conditions had 
taken shape for solving these problems, because "the potential 
of political stability in the life of society has increased and 
good mutual understanding has been established between the 
Federal Assembly and the president, including on that problem." 
  During his three-day visit to Russia, van der Stoel, who 
arrived in Moscow on Monday, also plans to meet Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev, Minister of the Affairs of Nationalities and 
Regional Policy Sergey Shakhray, and the chairmen of the 
parliamentary commissions on human rights and international 
affairs, Sergey Kovalev and Vladimir Lukin. 

</TEXT>

