<H3> <TI>   Churkin Leaves for Croatia-Krajina Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803103394 Moscow Radio 101 in Russian 1000 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2803103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio 101 </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vitaliy Churkin, special representative of the 
president of the Russian Federation, left for Zagreb today. A 
POSTFAKTUM correspondent was told at the Russian Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs that Vitaliy Churkin will take part in the 
second round of talks between Croatia and Serb Krajina. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

