<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Keeping Close Watch </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903101094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0756 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 29 Mar -- The Russian Federation Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs is keeping a close watch on the deteriorating 
situation in Algeria. A senior spokesman for the Russian 
Foreign Ministry told an ITAR-TASS correspondent that the 
Foreign Ministry is in constant contact with the Algerian side. 
He pointed out that the circumstances of the terrorist act 
against the Russian citizen are being investigated, and that 
exhaustive information from the Algerian side is expected on the 
affair. 

</TEXT>

