<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Signs Military Cooperation Treaty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803192994 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1700 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2803192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Video report by correspondent Sergey Zheleznyak, including </F>
recorded comment by Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev; from 
the "Novosti" newscast] 
  [Text] [Zheleznyak] A guard of honor welcomed the Russian 
defence minister in Bucharest today. Pavel Grachev's visit is 
evoking special interest here. I will recall that it was 
postponed twice, the last time because of the broad anti-Russian 
campaign started by the opposition last December. The 
cancellation of the visit obviously disappointed the official 
authorities at the time. For more than two years our countries 
did not have any agreements on military cooperation. Bucharest 
does not hide the fact that it sees its security only under 
NATO's roof. Romania was the first to sign the Partnership for 
Peace Treaty with it. At the same time, despite all kinds of 
statements on its striving toward military cooperation with the 
West, Romania understands perfectly well that it cannot do 
without an accord on military cooperation with its most powerful 
neighbor in the east. Today, Pavel Grachev and Romanian Defense 
Minister Gheorghe Tinca discussed and signed such a document. 
  [Grachev] It is a comprehensive treaty that presupposes a 
resumption of the most normal relations with the sovereign state 
of Romania. 
  [Zheleznyak] Technical cooperation is of special interest to 
Romania. Its Army is equipped with artillery, tanks, aircraft, 
and other Soviet-made hardware. The country has no money to 
replace it, but spares and ammunition are needed to keep the 
military hardware in operational condition. The Russian defense 
minister plans to attend military exercises and meet the 
president and prime minister of Romania. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

