<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Korean Group Demands End to `Provocation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2803151594 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 26 Mar 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PM2803151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Untitled "Own Information" report] </F>
  [Text] The Russian Association of Koreans "Bomminren" has 
made a statement in connection with recent events concerning the 
Korean peninsula which, due to the United States, have assumed a 
dangerous character. 
  Just recently, the statement says, the public greeted with 
satisfaction the news of an agreement being reached on a 
comprehensive solution for the so-called Korean nuclear 
question. Then suddenly the alarming news broke that the 
American side, using its dominant position in the International 
Atomic Energy Agency, had broken off all these agreements and 
made blunt threats against the DPRK which were accompanied by a 
stream of lies and slander aimed at North Korea. By so doing 
the United States and its allies revealed their true plans: 
Using the situation which had developed, they planned to 
slander and strangle the socialist state on Korean soil and 
prevent Korea's peaceful unification. 
  The Russian association "Bomminren" resolutely condemns the 
Americans' plans. On behalf of the many thousands of Koreans 
living in various countries outside of Korea it demands that the 
row and provocation connected with the so-called nuclear 
question on the Korean peninsula be stopped. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

