<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abkhazia Agrees on Talks at Russian Ministry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803142194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1252 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2803142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Brykin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 28 TASS--In response to the appeal of 
the Russian Government to resume talks between Abkhazia and 
Georgia on a peaceful settlement of the conflict, the Abkhazian 
side reiterated its readiness for talks. The Abkhazian 
leadership has always favoured a political settlement of 
controversial problems, the press service of the Abkhazian 
mission in Russia reported today. 
  The Georgian side also expressed readiness to resume talks. 
According to the Abkhazian press service, consultations at the 
Russian Foreign Ministry will probably begin this week. From 
the Abkhazian side they will be attended by Anri Dzhergenia, 
personal representative of the chairman of the Abkhazian Supreme 
Soviet, and Igor Abkha, official representative of the Republic 
of Abkhazia in Russia. 

</TEXT>

