<F P=100> Turkmenistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Outlines Armed Forces Reorganization Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3003092694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 2300 GMT 
29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3003092694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A reorganization of Turkmenistan's Armed Forces is 
soon to start in the Republic. The basic principles of the 
reorganization were set out at an expanded session of the 
country's Defense Council by President Saparmurad Niyazov. It 
provides for the establishment of the Defense Council and a 
National Security Council, a General Staff and Headquarters of 
the Armed Forces and rear services. The numerical strength of 
the country's Armed Forces is to be cut in line with the 
principle of essential defense sufficiency. Niyazov stressed 
the particular role of Russian officers in forming the Turkmen 
Army and noted the coincidence of the strategic interests of 
Turkmenistan and Russia. 

</TEXT>

