<H3> <TI>   Corruption Commission To Urge Dismissal of Top Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2903133794 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1207 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2903133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Supreme Soviet Interim Commission for Fighting 
Corruption has adopted a draft resolution that provides for 
dismissing Prime Minister Vyacheslaw Kebich, National Bank 
Chairman Stanislaw Bahdankevich, Deputy Prime Ministers 
Stanislaw Bryl and Mikalay Kostsikaw, Uladzimir Radkevich, 
chairman of the State Committee for External Economic Relations, 
and Defense Minister Pavel Kazlowski, "in connection with 
failing to adopt appropriate measures for protecting the 
economic interests of the state in relations with commercial 
organizations, as well as failing to enforce the existing law." 
The draft resolution was worked out at the 29 March meeting of 
the commission, and will submitted to the Supreme Soviet for 
consideration on 30 March, following a speech by Alyaksandr 
Lukashenka. As BELAPAN has learned, the commission has prepared 
a list of another 60 people to be dismissed. Among them is also 
Foreign Minister Petr Krawchanka. 

</TEXT>

