<H3> <TI>   Ministers Demand Official Opinion on Legitimacy of Charges </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2903185394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1715 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2903185394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We have received from BELINFORM the text of a 
declaration signed by two deputy prime ministers and the 
ministers of defense, foreign affairs, and external economic 
relations. In this declaration, the officials reject the 
accusations made public by People's Deputy Alyaksandr Lukashenka 
in various mass media. In this regard, the declaration's 
authors insist that the Belarusian prosecutor general publicly 
make an official written assessment of the legitimacy of 
Lukashenka's actions, the declaration emphasized, and the 
accuracy of information concerned their alleged activities. 

