<H3> <TI>   Presidential Elections Scheduled for 23 Jun </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS3003104394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1000 
GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS3003104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Supreme Soviet session is currently being held 
behind closed doors. As our correspondent has learned, deputies 
have focused their attention on the monetary-credit policy. 
Probably, we will be able to tell you about the adopted 
decisions, however, only approximately, because this issue, 
according to the parliament speaker, is secret. 
  This day can be considered, to certain degree, momentous in 
the work of the 13th session of the Supreme Soviet. Deputies 
have finally scheduled the presidential elections -- this event 
has been scheduled for 23 June 1994, for a regular working 
weekday. However, it used to be a regular working day -- it 
will be proclaimed a holiday, and we will have to make our 
choice. 
  At today's session, deputies also discussed legislation on 
the Belarusian Constitutional Court and adopted a resolution on 
implementing it. 

</TEXT>

