<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   President's Law on Elections Adopted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903172294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1659 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by BELINFORM for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk 29 Mar, TASS -- A law on elections of the 
Belarusian president was approved today in the second reading by 
215 parliament deputies to be introduced on Wednesday, 30 March. 
  Under the law, a citizen aging over 35, enjoying the 
electoral right and Belarusian resident for no less than ten 
years can be elected president for five years and no more than 
two terms. 
  The presidential elections shall be universal, equal and 
direct. The president shall be elected by Belarusian citizens 
aging over 18. 
  The right to nominate a presidential candidate will be 
enjoyed by those who manage to collect signatures of no less 
than 70 parliament deputies or no less than 100,000 signatures 
of Belarusian citizens. The nomination of presidential 
candidates shall start 75 days before the elections and end 40 
days before the voting. 
  Under the law, candidates for Belarusian president shall 
equally participate in the election campaign since the time of 
their registration by the central commission for presidential 
elections and enjoy equal rights to the use of mass media. 
  All the registered presidential candidates shall have equal 
possibilities of material-technical and financial provision of 
their election campaign. During the election campaign the 
candidates can be freed from their service duties and preserve 
an average salary. 
  If the ballot sheet includes no less than two presidential 
candidates and neither of them is elected, there will be 
repeated elections with repeated nomination of candidates. 
  The Belarusian president shall be considered elected if his 
candidature was supported by over 50 per cent of participants in 
the elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

