<F P=102>  LD2903152994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1540 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS nonstaff correspondent Anatoliy </F>
Kholodyuk] 
  [Text] Tiraspol (Dniester Province) 29 Mar, TASS -- The 
command of the 14th Russian Army deployed in Moldova's 
self-style Dniester Province, has warned Dniester leaders 
against what it called "political provocations." 
  The military command issued a statement on Tuesday [29 
March] 
retaliating a recent amendment to the Dniester laws which 
declared all Army weapons, equipment and other hardware 
belonging to Tiraspol. 
  "Tiraspol actually provokes seizure of the 14th Army's 
weapons and equipment," the statement said and qualified the 
actions of Dniester leaders as "demonstrating extreme disrespect 
towards the Russian Federation and its peace-keeping efforts in 
the region." 
  The Army command demanded the annulment of the "provocative" 
amendment. 

</TEXT>

