<F P=102>  AU2903150294 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1300 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2903150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The new parliament of the Republic of Moldova began 
its activity this morning. President Mircea Snegur, members of 
the government, representatives of diplomatic corps, and 
numerous journalists were present. 
  The report was read out on the final results of the 
elections 
and the Supreme Court decision regarding the approval of the 
elections. Then, the list was presented of the names of the 104 
deputies elected to the new parliament, among whom was Ilie 
Ilascu, a deputy for the Christian Democratic Popular Front 
Alliance, who could not be present because he is still 
imprisoned. 
