<F P=102>  NC3003061994 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1900 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC3003061994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1900 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Grant Bagratyan today received the 
U.S. Ambassador to Armenia Harry Gilmore, with whom he discussed 
economic issues. The improvement in the taxation system and 
American experts' assistance in this direction, the American 
contribution to spring agricultural work, and other problems 
were discussed. They also touched upon ways to find a political 
settlement to the Karabakh conflict. The CSCE Minsk Group and 
Russia's important efforts in this regard were stressed. 
  The prime minister also referred to the reoperation of the 
Armenian nuclear plant and to the position of the U.S. official 
organs. 
  The ambassador noted that those Americans opposing the 
reopening of the Armenian nuclear plant are not informed about 
the power situation in Armenia. They are worried that the 
safety of the nuclear plant is not up to the desired level 
therefore they will not assist with its reopening. 
  Gilmore handed Bagratyan a letter from the president of the 
International Organization of Science and Technology inviting 
Armenia to join the international organization. 

</TEXT>

