<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iraqi Compliance With International Demands Urged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903210994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1609 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Iraq should take more energetic steps to carry out 
the unimplemented demands of the international community. Only 
this will open up prospects for breaking the international 
isolation of Baghdad. The statement was made at a Tuesday 
briefing in Moscow by the official spokesman for the Russian 
Foreign Ministry Grigoriy Karasin. 
  According to him, Moscow has taken notice of the report of 
the UN Security Council Commission for the Disarmament of Iraq 
saying that the destruction of the Iraqi arsenal of chemical 
weapons is entering the final stage. The Commission Chairman 
Ralph Ekeus said that by now the bulk of chemical weapons has 
been scrapped and the necessary barriers have been built for the 
prevention of their production in the future. 
  "On the whole, this can be considered as additional 
confirmation of Baghdad's readiness to cooperate with the United 
Nations in implementing Security Council resolutions on the 
Persian Gulf. Such changes in the Iraqi approach should be 
encouraged. The call was made by the Russian ambassador to the 
United Nations during a recent Security Council debate on 
anti-Iraqi sanctions," Karasin said. 
  In his opinion, to prevent the possibility of the 
reconstruction of the Iraqi military potential, the mechanism of 
long-term monitoring should be launched as soon as possible and 
a trial period declared to check its efficiency. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

