<H3> <TI>   Border Cooperation Agreed On With Hungary, Romania </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903222694 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2000 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903222694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev--The press service of Ukraine's border troops 
reported on 29 March that a trilateral meeting of the heads of 
the border troops of Ukraine, Hungary, and Romania in the 
Hungarian town of Nyiregyhaza had ended. In accordance with a 
proposal by Army General Valeriy Hubenko, head of the Ukrainian 
delegation, a decision was made at the meeting to set up a joint 
coordinative group of the three countries for the cooperation of 
border troops in the campaign against illegal migration and 
organized crime. 

</TEXT>

