<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Fleet Demands Ukrainian Army Pay Debts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903185394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1837 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903185394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Mikhail Stetsyuk for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Sevastopol 29 Mar, TASS -- The command of the 
Crimea-based Black Sea Fleet has demanded that the Ukrainian 
Army pay its debts for electric power supplies and construction 
works provided by the fleet. 
  A message sent Tuesday to Ukrainian Defence Minister Vitaliy 
Radetskyy mentioned that the Ukrainian Army debts to the fleet 
amounted to 20 billion karbovanets (about 0.6 million dollars). 
  In case the debts are not settled before 10 April, the 
command will consider abandoning all construction works at the 
Ukrainian military sites and cutting off power supplies for the 
units of the Ukrainian Armed Forces, the message said. 

</TEXT>

