<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Does Not Want CIS Representation at UN </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903221194 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2000 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903221194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today, Yuriy Serhyeyev, head of the [Foreign 
Ministry] Information Directorate, reported at a Defense 
Ministry briefing that the Foreign Affairs Ministry is once 
again asserting that Ukraine does not need the mediation of a 
CIS representative to represent its interests at the United 
Nations. Ukraine's positions, which Volodymyr Handohiy 
[Ukraine's acting permanent representative at the United 
Nations] related at a plenary session of the UN General Assembly 
-- that a CIS representative can only represent the interests of 
those states that have signed the CIS Charter -- remain 
unchanged. As Ukraine has not done this, and also does not 
consider the CIS to be a subject of international law, but only 
a regional organization, Ukrainian diplomacy is in favor of 
direct and not mediated relations with the United Nations. 

</TEXT>

