<H3> <TI>   Riga To Protest Russian Servicemen's Conduct </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS3003095094 Tallinn BNS in English 1756 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS3003095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Mar 29, BNS -- Latvia is sending Russia a 
note of protest in view of a recent incident between Russian 
military persons and Latvian Homeguards, during which a series 
of illegalities were detected in the conduct of Russian 
servicemen. 
  The incident occured March 16 in the Riga district Stopini 
firing ground situated outside the territory of a nearby 
Russian military base. 
  The Russian servicemen had staged field excercise on the 
firing ground without a permit from the local authority, neither 
had they movement permits from the bureau monitoring the troop 
withdrawal. The incident was settled peacefully and the detained 
servicemen returned to their unit. 
  According to the note, Latvia hopes that similar incidents, 
which may have serious consequences, will be averted in the 
future. 
  Latvian Foreign Ministry's Aivars Vovers invited Russian 
diplomat Valeri Nesterushkin Tuesday [29 March] to receive the 
note. 

</TEXT>

