<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Crowd of 200' Protests Russian Troop Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2903185294 Tallinn BNS in English 1646 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2903185294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Mar 29, BNS -- A crowd of 200 gathered in 
front of the Cabinet building in Riga Tuesday [29 March] to 
protest the Latvian-Russian tentative agreement on troop 
withdrawal. 
  The meeting was organized by the Tevzeme (Fatherland) 
national association which dislikes the initialed agreement 
because it stipulates temporary functioning of a 
Russian-operated radar facility and guarantees rights of Russian 
war pensioners in the Baltic country. 
  The picket held slogans "The Oppressors Should Not Stay on 
the Land of the Oppressed," "Latvia No Resort for Russian 
Officers," chanting "Down with Government that Sells the Latvian 
Nation" and "Occupants -- Get Out." 
  The demonstrators demanded Prime Minister Valdis Birkavs or 
Special Tasks Minister Edvins Inkens to come out and speak on 
their record in front of the rally. But the officials did not 
appear. 
  Latvian National Independence Movement leader Aristids 
Lembergs was present in the meeting. Lembergs said that the 
agreements have not been ratified in the Saeima (parliament) yet 
and they bear no signature of the Latvian president. 
Consequently, the picket may help to form the opinion of 
deputies, he added. 
  The Cabinet is discussing the withdrawal agreement today. 

</TEXT>

