<H3> <TI>   Most Weapons Said Removed From Russian Division </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2903123894 Tallinn BNS in English 0850 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2903123894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Mar 29, BNS -- Practically all offensive 
weapons have been removed from the Tallinn-based Russian 144th 
motorized rifle division, a high-ranking official from the 
Estonian Defense Ministry told BNS on condition of anonymity. 
  The Defense Ministry has information that a troop train with 
the last remaining armored equipment of the 144th division 
leaves Estonia at the beginning of April. The number of means 
of transport and men in the division is not known. 
  The Russian division has to date turned over to Estonia the 
practice range at Aegviidu and the car repair shop in Tallinn. 
The facilities in Klooga, Keila and Tallinn are due to be 
handed over to the Defense Ministry later this spring. 

