<H3> <TI>   Official Discusses Cooperation With France </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2903123794 Tallinn BNS in English 0850 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2903123794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Mar 29, BNS -- Estonia and France may soon 
conclude an agreement on cooperation in defense, was the outcome 
of a meeting yesterday between Estonian Defense Ministry 
Chancellor Hannes Walter and officials from the French Defense 
Ministry east European department and the French Foreign 
Ministry. 
  Walter said at the meeting that, in his view, there are no 
blocks in the way of extending military cooperation between 
Estonia and France. The bilateral agreement on defense 
cooperation is ready to be signed, the Defense Ministry informs. 
  The members of the French delegation said at the meeting 
that 
after signing the defense cooperation agreement the two 
countries might discuss cooperation plans for next year and 
French-speaking Estonian officers' opportunities for studying at 
French military academies. 
  The French delegation also met with Col. Ants Laaneots, 
Estonian Defense Forces chief of staff, and head of naval 
department Capt. Roland Laid, and visited the National Defense 
Academy. 

</TEXT>

