<H3> <TI>   Danish Minister on Cooperation With Baltics </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903144194 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1200 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Estonian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Danish Defense Minister Hans Haekkerup is 
currently on a two-day visit to Estonia. Priit Ennet attended a 
news conference he gave at the airport. 
  [Ennet] Danish Defense Minister Hans Haekkerup intends to 
sign an Estonian-Danish defense cooperation agreement tomorrow. 
Denmark has already concluded similar agreements with Latvia 
and Lithuania. They envisage the holding of consultations in 
order to resolve defense and security issues and dialogue on 
strategic planning. Hans Haekkerup said on arrival at Tallinn 
airport that state defense greements with all Baltic states on 
state defense cooperation are basically very similar. 
  [Begin Haekkerup recording, in English fading to Estonian 
translation] It is important to us that the Baltic states should 
not be set to trail behind other central and eastern European 
countries. We wish to ensure that the Baltic states are part of 
Europe and have access to our security structures, with the help 
of bilateral and multipartite cooperation. We are much 
interested in cooperation with the Baltic peacekeeping 
battalion. The Nordic countries, in conjunction with other 
countries, have been aiming to draft a program of assistance to 
the Baltic battalion. We aim to help to design the battalion's 
structure and cooperate in training. I hope we will be able to 
supply some of the equipment. [passage omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

