Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Tallinn, March 29 -- Estonia's government thinks 
Herkki Haldre, the director general of state-owned Estonian 
Radio should be dismissed, Prime Minister Mart Laar told a news 
conference on Tuesday [29 March]. 
  The government supports the bill presented by the 
parliament's culture commission on dismissing the director 
general of the Estonian Radio, said Laar. 
  The chairman of the parliamentary commission presented the 
bill to Riigikogu [parliament] last Thursday after state 
auditors found "violations of finance discipline" in the radio. 

