<H3> <TI>   Preparations for Hand Grenades Production Begin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2803195694 Tallinn BNS in English 1559 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2803195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Mar 28, BNS -- Estonia is making 
preparations to start the production of hand grenades, Defense 
Ministry Deputy Chancellor Tarmo Molder told BNS. 
  Molder said a state-owned enterprise, a company with state 
participation and a private firm are involved in the project. 
  As next step, Estonia hopes to launch production of shells. 
  Manufacture of domestic cartridges was put off because of 
the 
high cost price. 
  Lithuania is at present the only Baltic nation to produce 
its 
own ammunition -- cartridges and hand grenades. The country 
plans soon to begin making 60 mm and 80 mm cannon and shells for 
them. The Latvian Defense Ministry has invited tenders for the 
manufacture of cartridges. 

</TEXT>

