<H3> <TI>   Armenian Attack on Agdamskiy Region Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2903145294 Baku TURAN in English 0945 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2903145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku (March 28) TURAN -- Last night the Armenian 
army launched an attack towards the Agdamskiy region of 
Azerbaijan, reports the press centre of Azerbaijan Defense 
Ministry. The Armenian army has 10 units of military hardware 
and 200 infantry-men. Earlier the Armenian army shelled 
positions belonging to the Azeri Army. The same source reports 
that the Azeri Army managed to thwart the attack and were able 
to liberate the villages of Garagashly and Shirvanly in the 
Agdamskiy region. The Armenian army lost military technique 
[equipment] as well as lives. 
  This morning the Armenian army launched an attack towards 
the 
village of Geytepe which is 10 km to the north-east of Agdam. 
The Azeri army destroyed one Armenian tank. Fighting in this 
direction continues. 
  Positions of the Azeri Army at the southern section of the 
front have been shelled as well. 
  At the same time villages in the Tauzskiy region of 
Azerbaijan have been shelled from Armenian's military bases 
located on the territory of Armenia's Berdskiy region. Damages 
have been reported. 

</TEXT>

