<H3> <TI>   Clashes Reported With Abkhazian Forces at Kodory </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2903163994 Yerevan SNARK in English 0758 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2903163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, March 29 (SNARK) -- Tension still exists at 
the Kodory ravine (Abkhazian Svanetia). Using helicopters 
Abkhazian side goes on with additional man power and military 
hardware transfer. Press-Service of the Georgian Defense 
Department told SNARK hard clashes are going on at the 
Kvemo-Lata village. Using artillery launchers, military 
hardware and howitzers Abkhazian side continues Georgian 
villages shelling. 
  Georgian side manages to repel the enemy. The Georgian 
volunteer forces lost 5 soldiers, 4 soldiers were wounded. 
Abkhazian side lost 60 soldiers. 
  As for the Zugdidi region, the situation is stable. No 
serious clashes took place. 

</TEXT>

