<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Denies Svanetia Occupied </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903190394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1831 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Georgian News Agency correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi March 29 TASS -- The Georgian Defence 
Ministry's press service refuted today an Abkhazian report 
claiming Abkhazians have occupied the whole of Abkhazian 
Svanetia. 
  According to information of the press service, position 
fighting goes on in the Kodor Ravine near the Verkhnyaya Lata 
settlement. The enemy has put Georgian positions under artillery 
and mortar fire and uses heavy materiel. 
  Some ten combat choppers have brought more personnel and 
materiel to the area, but the sides' positions have not been 
considerably changed within the past 24 hours. 
  The volunteers who have five killed and four wounded are 
repulsing the enemy who has lost up to 60 militants, reports the 
press center. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

