<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accord on Fishing development With EC Ratified </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903170594 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1600 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Seimas ratified an agreement today between the 
Republic of Lithuania and the European Economic Community on the 
development of fishing. 
  This agreement was signed in Brussels on 17 December 1993. 
The sides agreed to cooperate closer in the preservation and 
rational use of the stock of fish in the areas under the 
jurisdiction of both sides and the neighboring areas. The EEC 
promises to contribute to the improvement of the knowledge of 
the Lithuanian fishing industry workers and allocate financial 
assistance for their training. The agreement envisages that the 
sides will encourage the establishment of joint fishing industry 
enterprises. 

</TEXT>

