<H3> <TI>   Government Approves EBRD Plan on Enterprises </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903194694 Vilnius Radio Vilnius in English 1900 GMT 29 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Lithuanian Government has approved a proposal by 
the Bank for Reconstruction and Development in Europe [as heard 
-- EBRD] to carry out in Lithuania a program aimed at improving 
the financial and economic state of Lithuania's industrial 
enterprises. The program provides for the appropriation of up to 
2 million dollars to five state companies to make them 
competitive. 
  The Lithuanian Economics Ministry says the program has come 
too late and should have been put into effect about a year and a 
half ago. The main reason for this is the lack of medium-sized 
and still opportune enterprises, because the Reconstruction Bank 
does not want to finance very large companies. 

</TEXT>

