<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Denies Biological Weapons Development </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903204294 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 1943 GMT 29 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903204294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the Information and Press Department of the 
Russian Defense Ministry it has been said that the SUNDAY TIMES 
report referring to anonymous intelligence sources on the 
creation in Russia of a new biological weapon does not 
correspond to the facts. 
  Lieutenant General Valentin Yevstigneyev, deputy commander 
of 
troops for radiation shielding and chemical and biological 
warfare defense, stated that in accordance with the Russian 
president's Edict No. 390, dated 11 April 1992, all work running 
counter to the requirements of the 1972 convention banning 
biological weapons has been halted. 

</TEXT>

