<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chemical Weapon Destruction Research Going `Poorly' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2803075394 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 25 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2803075394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Aleksey Vorotnikov: "Chemists' Needs Not </F>
Understood"] 
  [Text] Saratov Oblast -- Scientists at the State Institute 
of Organic Synthesis Technology, which is in the settlement of 
Shikhany in Saratov Oblast, have discovered an interesting 
method of destroying chemical weapons. They have proposed using 
toxic agents as raw materials for the production of materials 
needed by the national economy. In particular, the Volga 
scientists plan to obtain arsenic from lewisite. They have 
managed to organize the production of medicines and household 
chemical products here. 
  However, the funding of research work in the destruction of 
lethal weapons is proceeding poorly. Last year, just 17 million 
rubles were allocated for this purpose. The chemical workers 
are bewildered. How can this be? 
  For several months now staffers at the institute have not 
received their wages and the enormous collective has been forced 
to take administrative leave without pay. How can there be any 
talk of getting rid of weapons when there is no money to pay for 
their destruction? 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

