<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Missile Incident Reveals `Unsuitable' Troops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2903185594 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 30 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2903185594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Viktor Sapov report: "Scarier Than the Caribbean Crisis. </F>
Nuclear Missiles Were in Criminal's Control"] 
  [Text] Barnaul -- An incident on a world scale occurred at 
a troop unit stationed in the vicinity of Barnaul. Private P., 
a native of Dagestan, shot a guard and seized a combat vehicle 
guarding missiles carrying nuclear warheads. You can imagine 
what the terrorist might have done had he reached the positions 
where the intercontinental ballistic missiles are held. 
  The regiment commander had difficulty persuading the soldier 
to surrender. Criminal proceedings have been instigated. But 
the conclusion is self-evident. Evidently, our valiant 
missilemen are having problems in obtaining fresh troops since 
unsuitable people are being admitted to secret installations. 

</TEXT>

