<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seventy Percent of Armed Forces Not Paid in Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903211094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1836 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903211094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A critical situation emerged in the Russian Armed 
Forces as officers and warrant officers did not receive their 
salaries. INTERFAX learned from sources close to the Russian 
Defense Ministry that the Finance Ministry had set aside only 30 
percent of the amount needed. Therefore, about 70 percent of 
officers and warrant officers were left without their pay for 
March. Many of them had not received their salaries for 
February either. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

