<H3> <TI>   Air Force Cuts Training Due to Lack of Fuel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903121694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1100 GMT 
29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Training flights have been considerably reduced at 
several air-defense units in the Far East, because of a shortage 
of fuel. The air-defense army headquarters told Interfax that 
unless fuel supplies are sorted out, fighter-interceptors will 
soon only be able to take off on an occasional basis and 
training plans will have to be cancelled altogether. 

</TEXT>

