<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accusations of `Crude' Election Violations in Crimea </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3003113694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3003113694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The situation in Crimea will deteriorate further. 
Yuriy Meshkov and his administration and the newly-elected 
Supreme Council will not be able to work constructively at 
maintaining peace and stability on the peninsula, says a 
statement by the Ukrainian sociopolitical organizations of 
Crimea and the Crimean Tatar National Rukh. This document is 
devoted to the outcome of the elections of 27 March in Ukraine. 
  The organization of the Crimean Tatar National Rukh will 
support the Ukrainian organizations in questions of maintenance 
of territorial integrity and affirmation of Ukrainian power on 
the territory of Crimea, the statement says. The authors of the 
document cite cases of a crude breach of legislation on the 
peninsula in the course of the election campaign and the 
elections themselves, but the greatest breach noted in the 
statement was the canvassing speech by the president on the eve 
of the elections on local TV. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

