<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thirty-Eight Percent of Electorate Voted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3003084894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0815 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3003084894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 30 TASS -- According to the specified, 
but still preliminary information, 38 per cent of the electorate 
took part in the Sunday elections to the representative bodies 
of power in subjects of the federation, a spokesman for the 
department for work with the territories at the president's 
administration told ITAR-TASS. Elections can be regarded as 
valid, if 25 per cent of electors took part in them, but still 
the activity of the population can hardly be described as high, 
although it is a little higher than during the previous stages 
of the electoral campaign. 
  In eight regions the voter turnout was more than 40 per 
cent. 
The figure was 63 per cent in the Ust-Ordynsky Autonomous 
District of Buryatia, which was the peak of activity. The 
population of two other autonomous districts also showed high 
activity: The representative bodies of power were fully formed 
in the Taymyr Peninsula and in the Evenk Autonomous District. 
  Activity was the lowest in the Samara and Magadan regions -- 
23 and 27 per cent respectively. Local dumas were not formed 
there. 

</TEXT>

