<H3> <TI>   Shakhray Accused of Manipulation in Chechnya </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903122094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1030 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chechen State Secretary Aslanbek Akbulatov has 
accused Russian Minister for Nationalities and Regional Policies 
Sergey Shakhray of manipulating the Chechen problem for the sake 
of bolstering his political image. "It is outrageous to be 
trying to influence the developments in Chechnya from Moscow, 
not knowing the actual situation and alignment of political 
forces here," he told Interfax. 
  He said he was referring to Shakhray's recommendation 
concerning the Russian leadership's contacts with forces 
opposing President Dudayev. 
  "The Chechen leaders' attitude to such recommendations is 
far 
from positive. They believe that such a position may jeopardize 
the recently established dialogue," he added. 
  "I wouldn't like to think that all this is being done 
deliberately. I can say, however, that there is very much in 
common between the demands of individual Chechen opposition 
leaders and the recommendations of the Russian minister," 
Akbulatov said in conclusion. 

</TEXT>

