<F P=102>  LD2903150894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1241 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By freelance correspondent Anatoliy Kholodyuk for ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Tiraspol, 29 Mar -- The 14th Army Military Council 
describes as a political provocation an amendment made on 15 
February to the unrecognised Dniester republic's law on the 
status of Russian troops stationed within the republic. 
According to the document, Russian troops' weapons, fighting 
equipment and other military property are declared the property 
of Tiraspol. 
  A statement by the Army Military Council issued today says 
that the Dniester authorities have demonstrated utter contempt 
of the Russian Federation and its efforts to uphold peace in the 
region. 
  Announcing that Tiraspol "is at state level encouraging the 
seizure of the 14th Army's sites, armaments and hardware," the 
military council of the Russian amalgamation of guards has 
lodged a strong protest with the Dniester authorities and demand 
that the law in question be repealed. 

</TEXT>

