<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Voronezh Facing Economic `State of Emergency' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2903150594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 29 Mar 94 
First Edition p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PM2903150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Yevgeniy Pisarev: "Administration Orders </F>
Stabilization"] 
  [Text] A state of emergency has been declared in Voronezh 
Oblast in order to stabilize finances in the social sphere, 
industry, and transport. In this connection Aleksandr Kovalev, 
head of the oblast administration, has signed several decrees 
instructing the financial administration to regulate the rayon 
and city budgets and thus, it is planned, even out the oblast 
budget deficit. 
  During the state of emergency period health care, education, 
social security, culture, and managerial structures will be on 
starvation rations -- they will be given the minimum funds 
needed to survive. Proposals aimed at cutting spending in these 
spheres are being given all kinds of backing. 
  The state tax inspectorate and the tax police have been 
given 
total carte-blanche. They have been ordered to step up checks 
to ensure that the oblast and local budgets receive full and 
timely revenue payments. 
  In effect Voronezh Oblast has decided to strengthen 
financial 
discipline by administrative means, tightening the screws in the 
loose reform mechanisms. On the other hand, evening out the 
budget deficit may be seen as a move toward retreat. I remember 
that censored military reports used to refer to a retreat as 
evening out the front line. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

