<H3> <TI>   Krasnodar To Begin Visa Regime for Republics </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903182794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1808 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2903182794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Viktor Zhilyakov] </F>
  [Text] Krasnodar March 29 TASS -- The Krasnodar Territorial 
administration has decided to introduce a visa regime for 
residents of the former soviet republics as the territory is a 
border area on the Russian south. 
  Speakers at today's meeting of the territorial 
administration 
noted that the Kubans have managed to organize the protection of 
borders and public safety in the territorial border areas 
bearing in mind the on-going clashes in the Transcaucasian and 
North Caucasian republics. 
  They have formed check points and mobile groups. Cossack 
organizations have made 130 units to participate in operations 
together with the local police. 
  Russian Interior Minister Viktor Yerin told the meeting that 
the escalation of violence in the Krasnodar Territory has become 
stable and criminal terror has turned regular. Last year alone 
the Kuban police revealed 400 criminal groups with an overall 
strength of 1,000 people. 

</TEXT>

