<F P=102>  LD3003112594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1029 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3003112594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Irina Bolshova and </F>
Vladimir Kikilo] 
  [Text] Moscow March 30 TASS -- "We want real cooperation, 
not an ostentatious one," President Boris Yeltsin said on 
Wednesday when receiving a U.S. business delegation led by 
Secretary of Commerce Ronald Brown, Russian Minister for Foreign 
Economic Relations Oleg Davydov told ITAR-TASS. 
  Davydov is attending the current session of the 
American-Russian Committee for the Development of Business 
Cooperation at President-Hotel here. 
  Four Russian-U.S. trade documents are expected to be signed 
at the session, Davydov said. These are: 
  -- regulations for a committee on the development of 
Russian-U.S. business cooperation, 
  -- regulations for the establishment of American business 
centres, to be funded by the U.S., 
  -- a joint statement on Russian commodities' access to the 
American market and of American ones to the Russian market, on 
the training of personnel and standardisation, 
  -- an agreement on terms for the supply of American 
medicines 
to the Russian market. 

