<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Results of Nagorno-Karabakh Talks Detailed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2903182694 Baku TURAN in English 1608 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2903182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku (March 29) TURAN -- The meeting of Azerbaijan's 
and Armenia's experts as well as the representatives of Armenian 
and Azeri communities of Nagorno-Karabakh took place on March 
20-25 through the mediation of Russian Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs. The talks were chaired by Russian President's special 
envoy on the settlement of the Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict, 
Vladimir Kazimirov. Deputy Chairman of the CSCE Minsk Group, 
Mathias Mosberg, and the leaders of the CSCE monitoring mission, 
General Burg and Berkman also participated at the meeting. 
  The expert of Azeri delegation, Tofik Zulfugarov, told TURAN 
that the mediator presented its draft of the agreement to both 
parties. 
  The draft stipulates for cease-fire and liberation of 
territories occupied by Armenia. 
  "It was difficult to find agreements with Armenia since it 
does not wish to liberate Kelbadzharskiy and Lachinskiy regions 
of Azerbaijan. The experts discussed the draft of the agreement 
proposed by Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs. The draft must 
be reviewed by the mediator taking into account several 
amendments and then will be presented to Azerbaijan's and 
Armenia's top powers as well as to the leaders of Azerbaijan's 
and Armenia's communities of Karabakh", said Zulfugarov. 
  Armenian experts insisted on liberation of a part of 
Azerbaijan's occupied territories with exception of Lachinskiy 
and Kelbadzharskiy regions. Those two regions will be liberated 
if Nagorno-Karabakh exists as a sovereign republic. 
  Azeri party offered the opposite, that is liberation of all 
territories occupied by Armenian troops and then Azerbaijan's 
and Armenia's communities will decide the matter concerning the 
status of Nagorno-Karabakh themselves. However, territorial 
integrity of Azerbaijan must be maintained. 
  Last week [as received] Kazimirov's and Mosberg's missions 
will arrive in Azerbaijan, reports Azerbaijan Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

