<H3> <TI>   Opposition Popular Front Nominates Paznyak </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS3003170994 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1600 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS3003170994 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a meeting that took place at the Belarusian 
Supreme Soviet on 30 March, the opposition Belarusian Popular 
Front [BNF] decided to nominate Zyanon Paznyak as its 
presidential candidate. At a press conference on the same day, 
BNF representative Syarhey Navumchik said that signatures in 
favor of Z. Paznyak will be collected among Supreme Soviet 
deputies and Belarusian citizens. In the words of S. Navumchik, 
while one should not count on support from the deputies, the 
signature drive among citizens might bring very good results. 
According to S. Navumchik, activists from the Free Trade Union 
are conducting a survey among workers at several enterprises to 
single out the most popular presidential candidates. Initial 
results are as follows: of 800 workers at the Minsk Tractor 
Plant, only one person each spoke in favor of Stanislav 
Shushkevich and Alyaksandr Lukashenka, while the other 798 
respondents expressed support for Zyanon Paznyak. 

</TEXT>

