<F P=103> LD3003163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by BELINFORM correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 30 March (TASS) -- The Belarusian Popular 
Front officially nominated on Wednesday its candidate for the 
upcoming presidential elections. 
  The presidential nominee is Zenon Poznyak, the front's 
leader 
and a people's deputy, coordinator of the parliamentary 
opposition Sergey Naumchik told a briefing in parliament. He 
noted that as soon as all the necessary formalities are 
completed, the Belarusian Popular Front will get down to 
collection of signatures in support of Poznyak. 

