<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lukashenka Presents Corruption Report, Demands Resignations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS3003191894 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1900 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS3003191894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 30 March, Alyaksandr Lukashenka, head of the 
legislative anticorruption commission, delivered a report at the 
evening sitting of the 13th Belarusian Supreme Soviet session in 
Minsk. He said that his commission has demanded the resignation 
of Deputy Prime Ministers Mikalay Kostsikaw and Stanislaw Bryl; 
Uladzimir Radkevich, head of the State Committee for Foreign 
Economic Relations; chairman of the Board of the Belarusian 
National Bank [Stanislaw Bahdankevich]; and Defense Minister 
Pavel Kazlowski. However, A. Lukashenka did not present 
specific facts, except in the case of Deputy Prime Minister 
Stanislav Bryl. According to Lukashenka, S. Bryl pulled some 
strings so that his son could receive a plot of land on which to 
build a house. Deputy Prime Minister Mikalay Kostsikaw was one 
of the people on Lukashenka's list that took advantage of 
services rendered by the governments's renovation and 
construction administration, and failed to pay the entire amount 
of money charged by the administration. In addition, A. 
Lukashenka said that his commission sent a letter to Belarusian 
Prosecutor General Vasiliy Shaladonov with the request to see 
that individuals mentioned earlier in the commission's report be 
persecuted. There are 54 officials, including Foreign Minister 
Pyotr Krawchanka, named in the report. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

