<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supreme Soviet Rejects Governement Draft on Monetary Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS3103092894 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1000 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS3103092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] At its 30 March closed session, the Supreme 
Soviet did not pass any resolution regarding the main directions 
of the monetary-credit policy in 1994. National Bank Chairman 
Stanislaw Bahdankevich pointed out at a news conference that the 
National Bank and the Council of Ministers had drafted a joint 
resolution suggesting that the main directions of the 
monetary-credit policy be adopted; the National Bank's payment 
bill be proclaimed the only legal tender on Belarusian territory 
for the period preceding the final merging of the Russian and 
Belarusian monetary systems; the National Bank's motion on 
commercial banks be confirmed. The motion envisions that 
commercial banks earmark at least 13 percent of their credit 
capital for the implementation of promising investment projects. 
  However, this draft along with other proposals by some 
people's deputies was rejected by the Supreme Soviet.[passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

