<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leftist DSPS: Vouchers Will Strip Workers of Social Rights </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS3103103194 Minsk RID in Russian 1000 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS3103103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk RID </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In connection with the Supreme Soviet resolution 
regarding the issuance of personal privatization vouchers as of 
1 April 1994, the Republican Council of the Movement for 
Democracy, Social Progress, and Justice [DSPS] has addressed 
workers, peasants, and the working intelligentsia with an appeal 
to join the DSPS and resolutely demand that the state's economic 
course be altered. According to the appeal, the actual aim of 
personal vouchers is "to strip us of national property and of 
such social guarantees as the right to work, rest, happy 
childhood, adequate care in old age, free medical care, and 
housing." 
  The authors of the document believe that the project of 
issuing vouchers is "the final stage of transforming the 
socialist socioeconomic system into a capitalist one, which 
entails such inevitable consequences for working people as 
poverty, absence of rights, unemployment and diseases, 
humiliation, and the tragedy of colonial dependence." 
  The DSPS Republican Council calls upon the Belarusian 
Supreme 
Soviet to reject privatization and offers another way to 
overcome the crisis. In particular, it suggests that DSPS 
candidates be elected to the legislature and local soviets; and 
that the constitution adopted against people's will, be 
rescinded. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

