<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Snegur Dismisses Claims Russian Speakers Leaving </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM3103095794 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 30 Mar 94 p 
3 </F>

<F P=103> PM3103095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [INTERFAX report: "Moldavian President Denies Rumors of the </F>
Migration of Russian-Speaking Population"] 
  [Text] Rumors circulating about the migration from 
Moldavia [Moldova] of the Russian-speaking population have no 
real basis, Republic President Mircea Snegur stated. He 
described them as tendentious. Meeting on Monday [28 March] 
with leaders of Tarakliyskiy Rayon, where there is a concentated 
population of Bulgarians, M. Snegur also touched on the 
certification of the population in the knowledge of the state 
language, scheduled for 2 April. In his opinion, the timetable 
for this should be finally examined by the new parliament. 
  At the same time, the president believes that the necessary 
conditions should be created for study of the state language, 
and that the state is seeing to this. M. Snegur remarked that 
knowledge of the state language for people occupying leading 
posts is obligatory. 

</TEXT>

