<H3> <TI>   Meshkov Issues Decree on National Minorities Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3003210494 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2245 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3003210494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Simferopol, 29 Mar--Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov 
has issued a decree on a mechanism to implement the law on 
national minorities. In accordance with the decree, a 
commission has been set up that is to prepare materials on 
implementing the rights of citizens to have their national 
surnames, first names, and patronymics, and to restore their 
nationality in documents. Anife Seytomer-Kyzy, adviser to the 
president of Crimea on international relations, is head of the 
commission. 

</TEXT>

