<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kuchma Urges Early Adoption of Taxation Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3003143594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1314 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3003143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The first law which the new parliament should adopt 
is a law on taxation. This statement was made in an interview 
with Interfax-Ukraine, by the co-chairman of the inter-regional 
bloc of reforms, Leonid Kuchma. 
  He was elected on March 27 to be people's deputy of Ukraine, 
winning in his constituency 91 percent of the votes. 
  Kuchma believes that the legal basis was virtually destroyed 
in economics. He criticized the activities of the government 
which in December 1993 freed prices and restricted credits. 
According to the former prime minister, this has caused the 
debt crisis and the stoppage of enterprises. 
  He still believes that the president should be the head of 
the executive power. He disagrees that the heads of the local 
councils be granted executive powers. 
  "On this I agree with Kravchuk. If so, we will really have 
26 presidents in 26 regions," said Kuchma. 
  He spoke against rescheduling the presidential elections for 
a later date. There are no grounds for that, he said. 
  Speaking about the problem of relations between the Crimea 
and Ukraine, Kuchma said that pressure on Crimea will produce no 
results. 
  Crimea should be a starting point for reforms in Ukraine, 
said Kuchma. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

