<F P=102>  LD3103113394 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1100 GMT 31 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3103113394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi IBERIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, 31 Mar -- According to IBERIA news agency, 
today employees of the Tbilisi Police Department gathered at the 
Parliament building. About 500 of them remained outside the 
building while approximately 300 entered the parliament building. 
  After confirmation by Parliament of Shota Kviraya as the 
interior minister of the Republic of Georgia, the police 
employees started knocking at the door, demanding that the head 
of state come outside. 
  There were clashes between the head of state's security 
guard 
and police when Shevardnadze came out of the parliament 
building. Tbilisi police department chief David Zeikidze accused 
Shevardnadze of breaking his promise and demanded that the case 
of the interior minister be revised. 
  Negotiations were held between the head of the Georgian 
state 
and the representatives of the Tbilisi Police department. A 
certain agreement has been reached. Negotiations are still 
continuing (by 1345). 

