  [Text] Tbilisi 31 Mar, TASS -- A big group of policemen 
headed by Chief Police Officer of Tbilisi, Major General David 
Zeikidze attempted on Thursday to break into the assembly hall 
of the Georgian Parliament to protest against the planned 
appointment of Shota Kviraya as the new interior minister. 
