<F P=103> LD3003144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The press service of the Abkhazian mission in Moscow 
has denied Georgian sources' reports about fighting in 
Abkhazia's Kodor Ravine. 
  With reference to the Abkhazian Defense Ministry, an 
Abkhazian spokesman told INTERFAX that fighting continued from 
24 March to 26 March, during which Abkhazians occupied the 
village of Lata, the Georgian stronghold in this region. 
  He said, however, that individual clashes were not ruled 
out. 
  He rejected Georgian sources' assertions that 60 Abkhazian 
soldiers were killed on 29 March. Two Abkhazians have been 
killed since fighting began, he said. 

