<H3> <TI>   Report Successful Operation in Kodor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3003175294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1611 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD3003175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vladislav Ardzinba, chairman of the Abkhazian 
parliament, held a conference in Sukhumi on 30 March to report 
on the operation to eliminate Georgian saboteur groups active in 
the Kodor canyon, the parliament's press service reported. The 
conference was attended by Abkhazian Deputy Prime Minister 
Vladimir Mikanba and top officials of the Defense and Interior 
Ministries and the security service. 
  An attack by Georgian gangs was said to have been beaten 
back 
and several armored vehicles and small arms and a large amount 
of ammunition captured. The village of Lata, Gulripsh District, 
was liberated. 
  The press service also reported that remains had been found 
of passengers of a helicopter that had flown on a humanitarian 
mission from the besieged town of Tkvarcheli to Gudauta when it 
had been shot down by the Georgians in the vicinity of Lata on 
14 December 1992. 
  According to Abkhazian Deputy Defense Minister Nikolay 
Jonua, 
"the situation in the Kodor canyon has stabilized and no 
hostilities are underway other than local exchanges of fire with 
remnants of Georgian units that have escaped up the Kodor 
canyon." 

</TEXT>

