<H3> <TI>   Chief Russian Negotiator Says Positive Results Possible </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS3003195694 Tallinn ETA in English 1758 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS3003195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Tallinn, March 30 -- Head of Russian delegation at 
Estonian-Russian inter-state negotiations Vasiliy Svirin told 
ETA, on Wednesday [30 March], that the Russian side had "done 
serious work during the last weeks to continue constructive 
discussions at the 18th round of negotiations" due on April 5-6 
in Moscow, and if similar approach was used by the Estonian side 
positive results at the forthcoming round could be hoped for. 
  "We hope that the Estonian side thought over the results of 
the 17th round and came to the conclusion that we have to find 
ways to compromise to solve some of the deadlocks," he said. 
  On Thursday, Estonian Decolonization Initiative Centre will 
hold a picket in front of the building of Estonian Foreign 
Ministry to support and encourage Estonian delegation before the 
18th round. "Estonian delegation should not choose the Latvian 
way on the issue of the retired Russian military, but has to 
lift up its chin," Juri Estam from the Center told ETA. 

</TEXT>

