<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Popular Concord Party Supports Withdrawal Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS3003194894 Tallinn BNS in English 1843 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS3003194894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Mar 30, BNS -- The signature and ratification 
of the agreement with Russia on troop withdrawal is in the 
interests of the Latvian security and sovereignty, the 
provisional board of the Popular Concord Party said Wednesday 
[30 March]. 
  The party says it cannot understand why the preparation of 
the agreements was delayed for two years, thus, losing the time 
when the agreement could have been based on terms more 
advantageous to Latvia. 
  The party is surprised why international experts have not 
unveiled their views on the environmental and health effect of 
the Skrunda radar yet. The findings missing, the radar facility 
has become an object of conflicts and political speculations. 
  The issue of the amount of rent for the radar's functioning 
should not be left only with the presidents of Latvia and Russia 
because the Latvian Constitution grants the country's president 
no such prerogative. The party wants Prime Minister Valdis 
Birkavs to also sign the anticipated rent contract. 

</TEXT>

