Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Mar 30, BNS -- The Latvian Cabinet adopted a 
resolution Tuesday [29 March] on the foundation of a 
Privatization Agency and confirmed its statutes. 
  The government also commissioned State Reforms Minister to 
organize Latvia's entrance to the International Institute of 
Administrative Sciences. 
  In addition, the ministers passed a proposal to the Saeima 
(parliament) on the ratification of the 1963 Vienna convention 
on civil responsibility for nuclear damages and the 1988 common 
protocol on the use of Vienna and Paris conventions. 
  The government also passed for Saeima consideration a bill 
on 
radiation and nuclear safety, and approved a Latvian-Indian 
memorandum on cooperation in culture, science, education, 
information and sports. 

