<H3> <TI>   Fabbri Approves NATO Air Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2802123194 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1137 GMT 28 
Feb 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2802123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "NATO/Bosnia: Fabbri on Jet </F>
Downings"] 
  [Text] Rome, 28 Feb (ANSA) -- NATO pilots were acting in 
compliance with the no-fly zone resolution 816 of the United 
Nations when they shot down four fighter jets over Bosnia this 
morning, Italian Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri said. 
  "We are faced with a painful episode," Fabbri said, adding: 
"The fact remains that the international community and the 
United Nations want to make credible and coherent their 
willingness to guarantee global order and security, they cannot 
avoid the use of force with the aim of peace-making and 
providing humanitarian aid." 
  This, Fabbri said, is "the only way" the UN can maintain the 
authority and prestige necessary to keep the growing number of 
crisis areas around the world under control. 

</TEXT>

