<F P=101> Italy </F>
<H3> <TI>   Italy Leads in Joint Ventures With CIS </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2202151994 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1252 GMT 22 
Feb 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2202151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Italy a Leader in Joint Ventures </F>
With Ex-USSR"] 
  [Text] Rome, 22 Feb (ANSA) -- Some 13,000 joint ventures 
have so far been registered in the Soviet Union, and 8,200 of 
these are presently active, according to a survey made last 
October by the Italian publication SISTEMA ITALIA, the weekly of 
the Italian Trade Board and the Milan Chamber of Commerce. 
  The value of these joint ventures has been estimated at 3 
percent of the total industrial production of the Commonwealth 
of Independent States, while the value of joint venture exports 
for the first nine months of 1993 reached 3.2 billion dollars. 
  The main markets are Japan, Germany, Italy and the United 
States. According to SISTEMA ITALIA, foreign investments in 
Russia and other ex-Soviet republics equaled 7 billion dollars 
last fall. Sixty percent of the investors are Russian 
companies, followed by 20 percent who are Italians, and a 
smaller percentage of Austrians, Dutch and Belgians. 

</TEXT>

