<H3> <TI>   West Reacts to NATO's Downing of Serb Aircraft </TI></H3>
<H4>   FRG's SPD Welcomes Action </H4>
<F P=102> LD2802115094 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1118 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2802115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- In shooting down four Serb combat 
aircraft over Bosnia-Herzegovina, the United Nations has 
demonstrated its resolve not to let the budding peace process be 
destroyed, according to Social Democratic Party [SPD] leader 
Hans- Ulrich Klose. Klose said in Bonn today that the SPD 
welcomed and supported the no-fly zone imposed by the UN. The 
SPD hopes that consistent compliance with UN resolutions will be 
taken seriously by all Bosnian parties, thus improving the 
possibility of political solutions, Klose said. 

</TEXT>

