<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Western Leaders Comment on Hebron Mosque Massacre </TI></H3>
<H4>   FRG's Kohl, Kinkel Note `Devastation, Disgust' </H4>
<F P=102> LD2602144494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1347 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2602144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl and Foreign 
Minister Klaus Kinkel have noted the massacre of Palestinians 
yesterday in Hebron with "devastation and disgust." Today in 
Bonn, government spokesman Dieter Vogel said that the Federal 
Government conveyed its deepest sympathy to the relatives of the 
victims. It expressed the hope that the act of violence would 
not jeopardize the peace process between Israel and the PLO. 
All those responsible were called upon to prevent the violence 
from escalating. 

</TEXT>

