<H3> <TI>   EU Expansion Negotiations Continue in Brussels </TI></H3>
<H4>   Austria's Mock: `Crisis Has Arisen' </H4>
<F P=102> AU2802094694 Vienna Oesterreich Eins Radio Network in German 
0600 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2802094694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna Oesterreich Eins Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On officially the last day of Austria's negotiations 
for European Union [EU] membership the tough positions of the 
two sides remain unchanged. The major obstacles to a conclusion 
on schedule continue to be the issues of transit and agriculture. 
  Yesterday evening in Brussels, Foreign Minister Mock no 
longer ruled out the possibility that the talks might be broken 
off. He said literally that a crisis where one might go home 
has certainly arisen. Greek EU Chairman Pangalos said that he 
would deplore such a step very much. He did not want to rule 
out a successful conclusion of the negotiations despite the 
current crisis. 

</TEXT>

