<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   European Parliament Head Meets Iranian Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602192994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mahmud Va'ezi, the Iranian deputy foreign minister 
in charge of Euro-American affairs, accompanied by the Iranian 
ambassadors to Bonn and Brussels, met for discussions Egon 
Klepsch, the president of the European Parliament, at the 
parliament building in Brussels. 
  In the meeting, Mr. Va'ezi stressed the expansion of 
relations between the Islamic Republic of Iran and the European 
Parliament, and said such contacts were useful and effective for 
better mutual understanding. 
  Then Mr. Klepsch, referring to the significance and position 
of Iran in the region said: the Islamic Republic of Iran is an 
important country that could help solve regional crises and 
establish world peace and stability. 
  Finally the speaker of European Parliament said the 
establishment of a friendship committee between the European 
Parliament and Iran was necessary for the mutual understanding 
of both sides. 

</TEXT>

