<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliamentarian Hails Iran's Efforts for Peace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402135294 Tehran IRNA in English 0814 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2402135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, Feb. 24, IRNA -- Head of the German 
parliament's Foreign Affairs Commission Hans Stercken said 
Wednesday [23 February] that the world should appreciate Iran's 
efforts for the establishment of peace and tranquillity in the 
region. 
  In a meeting here with visiting Iranian Deputy Foreign 
Minister for Euro-American Affairs, Mahmud Va'ezi, Stercken 
noted that the German Government and parties shared the idea 
that friendly ties and cooperation with Iran should be continued. 
  The German official also called on Iran to play a more 
active 
role in solving Afghan issue and the regional crises and 
remarked that Iran had more power and authority to peacefully 
settle the crisis. 
  Va'ezi believed that the U.S. was the main obstacle on the 
way of materialization of a collective regional cooperation 
system as well as peace and security in the Persian Gulf. 
  He commented that the United States intended to drive the 
regional states closer to itself through sowing discord among 
Iran and his neighbors in order to sell them more weapons. 
  Pointing out that Iran had fully cooperated with the United 
Nations on Afghan issue, the Iranian diplomat noted that the 
international community, besides its humanitarian aids, should 
stop sending arms to the clashing groups in Afghanistan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

