<H3> <TI>   Deployment of Troops, Helpers in Bosnia Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602091194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0232 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2602091194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hamburg (DDP/ADN) -- According to a report in the 
news magazine DER SPIEGEL, the German Government is planning to 
send soldiers and civilian aid workers to war-torn Bosnia as 
soon as a peace settlement for the country is negotiated at a 
summit meeting. The magazine quotes planning papers by the 
German Chancellery, according to which a German administrator 
commissioned by the European Union is to rebuild the 
administration in the Croat-besieged Muslim stronghold of 
Mostar. German policemen and administrative officials could 
help the "emergency mayor." Under Bonn's plans, Bundeswehr 
medical officers are to operate the city's hospital and 
Bundeswehr engineers are to repair bridges and roads. 

</TEXT>

