<H3> <TI>   Government Calls Report `Speculation' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602120494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1124 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2602120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- A report in DER SPIEGEL news 
magazine saying that Bonn is planning to send soldiers and 
civilian helpers to Bosnia under a peace settlement has not been 
confirmed by the German Government. A Bonn government spokesman 
said today that DER SPIEGEL's information was "pure 
speculation." The plans cited by the magazine were not known to 
the Bonn Chancellery. 
  DER SPIEGEL had reported that a German administrator was to 
rebuild the administration in the Croat-besieged Muslim 
stronghold of Mostar on behalf of the European Union. German 
police and administrators were to assist the "emergency mayor." 
Under the Bonn plans, Bundeswehr medical officers were to run 
the city's hospital and Bundeswehr engineers were to repair 
bridges and roads. 

