<H3> <TI>   SPD Leader Backs 'Arafat in Peace Quest </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602152494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1418 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2602152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- SPD [Social Democratic Party] 
leader Rudolf Scharping has promised PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat 
his "unlimited support" in efforts toward a solution for peace 
in the Middle East. In Bonn today in a letter Scharping 
conveyed to 'Arafat his sympathy for the relatives of the 
Palestinians who were killed in a massacre in Hebron on Friday 
[25 February]. The SPD leader expressed his view that the 
attack meant a need for the speedy continuation of the peace 
negotiations in the Middle East. 

